South Africa has recorded 1 102 new cases of coronavirus on Monday, which increased the total number of confirmed cases to  1 492 909. In a statement, the Department of Health has also reported further 195 deaths. “Eastern Cape 25, Free State 11, Gauteng 58, Kwa-Zulu- Natal 3, North West 30, Northern Cape 6, and Western Cape 62. ” This brings the total to 48 094 deaths.  The recoveries now stand at 1 391 155, representing a recovery rate of 93%. The cumulative total of tests conducted to date is 8 712 844 with 15 778 new tests recorded since the last report. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 1 492 909 the total number of deaths is 48 094 and the total number of recoveries is 1 391 155. pic.twitter.com/8yYp2stPjA — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) February 15, 2021 